==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek meaning ''fate'', from ''moros'', (fate, destiny, doom, lot) from ''meiresthai'', (to receive one's share).

===Proper noun===
'''Moira'''

# (''Greek mythology''): The personification of fate.

